      <h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p><strong>Last updated on 26th March, 2023</strong></p>
      <p>
        At Student Square, we respect and protect the privacy of our users. This
        Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal
        information when you visit our website. By using our website, you
        consent to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p><strong>Personally Identifiable Information You Provide</strong></p>
      <p>
        Student Square collects personal information through our Services, both
        online and offline. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Student Programming:</strong> Information from students and
          parents.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Volunteer Applications:</strong> Contact and demographic
          information, citizenship status for background checks.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Job Applications:</strong> Relevant personal information for
          application purposes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Donations:</strong> Personal and financial information for
          processing donations.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Information Automatically Collected from Our Site</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Web Log Data:</strong> IP address, domain name, pages visited,
          and other online activity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Web Beacons:</strong> Used in emails and on the Site to track
          engagement.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookies:</strong> Used to recognize visitors and track usage
          behavior.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>Student Square values your privacy and uses your information for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Offering our programming</li>
        <li>Responding to inquiries</li>
        <li>Processing donations and applications</li>
        <li>Sending updates and promotional content</li>
        <li>Complying with legal requirements</li>
        <li>Analyzing site usage and improving services</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>With Whom and Why We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>We may share your information with third parties for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics:</strong> Using tools like Google Analytics to
          understand site usage.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Interest-Based Advertising:</strong> Targeted ads based on
          your site activity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal Purposes:</strong> Compliance with laws, preventing
          fraud, and protecting rights.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disability Inclusion and Equal Opportunity</h2>
      <p>
        We are committed to ensuring accessibility and inclusion for students
        with disabilities in our mental health services.
      </p>

      <h2>Ethical Fundraising Policy</h2>
      <p>
        All fundraising activities comply with relevant laws and respect donor
        privacy. We do not sell or disclose personal information collected
        during these activities.
      </p>

      <h2>Donor Privacy Statement</h2>
      <p>
        We hold donor information in strict confidence and use it only for
        communication regarding donations or Student Square events.
      </p>

      <h2>Credit Card Information Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use high-grade encryption and the HTTPS security protocol to protect
        your transaction information.
      </p>

      <h2>Fraud Control</h2>
      <p>
        We follow guidelines to prevent, identify, and address fraud, ensuring
        responsible use of our assets and maintaining public trust.
      </p>

      <h2>Transparency</h2>
      <p>
        We are committed to openness in our actions and decisions, providing
        timely and accurate information to our stakeholders.
      </p>

      <h2>Email Policy</h2>
      <p>
        To opt out of our email lists, use the unsubscribe link in our emails or
        contact us directly.
      </p>

      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <p>
        Our site may contain links to third-party websites. We are not
        responsible for their content or privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We employ measures to safeguard personal information but cannot ensure
        complete security. Information is stored in our secure Customer
        Relationship Management system, accessible only by authorized staff.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be posted
        on our website, and continued use of our site constitutes acceptance of
        these changes.
      </p>
